annotations: (Super emo, aqua girl with the rising Leo)

Remi Wolf’s star sign (also known as a sun sign) is an Aquarius, someone born between January 20 and February 18. According to Ranker, Aquarius' are a “classic mashup of a theater kid and an emo.”

In January 2022, Remi revealed that she wasn’t actually a Leo rising, but a Pisces rising. Pisces is a water sign, which are considered to be the most emotional of the signs.

Upon revealing her true rising sign, Remi tweeted:

https://twitter.com/remiwolf/status/1481803959090049026?s=20
Switch my Bug for a brand new Beamer
Ted Bundy owned a 1968 VW Beetle (Bug) and would lure his victims to his car in order to kidnap and eventually kill them.
(Not the hero, I’m the west coast Bob De Niro)
Bob De Niro refers to Robert De Niro, an acclaimed actor, producer and director born in Manhattan, New York. De Niro is known for playing violent, morally grey characters.
Billy Bob and Angelina

Billy Bob Thornton and Angelina Jolie were among the most-talked-about Hollywood celebrity couples in the early 2000s. Similar to Remi’s earlier line about drawing blood, the couple famously sliced their fingers and smeared their blood on lockets that they exchanged and wore around their necks at all times

I can move to Pasadena
 Just to be your serial killer, killer
Dean Arnold Corll (also known as the Candy Man and the Pied Piper) was a serial killer who murdered at least 28 teenage boys and young men between 1970 and 1973 in Houston and Pasadena, Texas.
Get my milk from Altadena

Alta Dena is a popular milk company that began in the Los Angeles area, named after the Altadena region on the northern outskirts of Los Angeles county. Altadena is right next to Pasadena, so Remi is likely making a joke that if she moved to Pasadena she could buy milk from the actual city, not just the brand.

Long as he don’t check the freezer
 Yum, yum, yum

Reference to the trope “Fridging your women” which originates from the Green Lantern comics. It is where a female character who is typically romantically involved, but can sometimes be a family member, is killed off only to serve the purpose of motivating the male protagonist on his journey. She’s saying the hero will like her as long as he doesn’t “check the freezer” aka, come to the realization she is the villian wreaking havoc on his life.

Remi alludes to real life serial killers earlier when she talks about going to Pasadena, therefore this line may not be based on fiction, but instead inspired by reality. Killers like Dahmer would store their victims in the freezer.
Left my boy watching Euphoria
Possibly refers to her friend Dominic Fike, who will be playing a role in Euphoria season 2 and has a really awesome verse on Photo ID.
(High libido, cheat on Chester, fuck with Fritos)

Chester the Cheetah is the mascot of a popular chip brand, Cheetos. Although under the same company, Frito-Lays are typically put against each other and are up for debate. In the lyrics, Remi shows that she would rather have fritos as opposed to taking cheetos.

description.plain:
“Disco Man” came out on May 27, 2020, and was the third single release off of Remi Wolf’s EP ‘I’m Allergic To Dogs!’, which was released in full on June 24, 2020.

Though Remi usually works with her co-producer Solomonophonic, this track actually came together differently as she explained to Invertebrate:

“Disco Man” was written with two other writers and they are just so talented and super awesome. They all made me feel really comfortable and we just wrote a great song.“
—Remi Wolf, via Invertebrate (June 2020)

annotations: He likes his cherries when they’re maraschino
These are preserved cherries with artificial red colourant, popular on cocktails and milkshakes (so this man probably likes a fancy drink)

And he’s never tongue tied, he’s alright
 Always dressed in black tie with white guys

Class is an important factor in confidence. “Black tie with white guys” refers to the disco man’s status: he most probably comes from old money and therefore is able to hang out with the social elite. The line reinforces the idea that the man is a part of the de facto aristocracy of the United States and therefore has the confidence to seem attractive to potential partners.
And he’s got a lot of fiscal plans
Fiscal means “relating to government revenue, especially taxes” so… I guess it just rhymed?
Gas station glasses on his way to Rio
The implication of this line that to describe the man Remi Wolf is singing about as someone who is either broke, carefree, or both
He likes his movies when they’re Tarantino

Quentin Tarantino is famous for a lot of notable movies like Pulp Fiction and Kill Bill.

Tarantino movies are typically raunchy and violent, hence why it’s more directed at a male audience.

description.plain: “I wanted to share ‘Liz’ as a gift to my little Remjobs who have been with me since the beginning and have been asking for this song everyday over the last few years. I’ve been performing ‘Liz’ on tour for forever and to finally have a studio version I’m proud of and can share with my OG babies feels like a weight has been lifted off my chest. This record shows a different side of my work. I felt so happy and free creating this song and I hope it makes whoever is listening feel the same.”

description.plain:
“Pink + White – Live at Electric Lady” is the penultimate track and only cover on American singer-songwriter Remi Wolf’s Spotify-exclusive live multitrack single, recorded at Electric Lady Studios. The arrangement was first stated to be featured on the single in a video uploaded to Instagram by Remi where she stated she would cover a Frank Ocean song, as the performance acts as Remi’s rendition of Ocean’s “Pink + White”.

It was released August 4th, 2022, alongside the rest of the Live at Electric Lady single.

“Pink + White – Live at Electric Lady” is the penultimate track and only cover on American singer-songwriter Remi Wolf’s Spotify-exclusive live multitrack single, recorded at Electric Lady Studios. The arrangement was first stated to be featured on the single in a video uploaded to Instagram by Remi where she stated she would cover a Frank Ocean song, as the performance acts as Remi’s rendition of Ocean’s “Pink + White”.

It was released August 4th, 2022, alongside the rest of the Live at Electric Lady single.

annotations: She touched down on London ground
In an Instagram post on November 9, 2021, Remi Wolf wrote that she had landed in London for her tour’s 2 UK shows. This presumably happened soon after meeting with Sven.
Crying ’bout how much he loves his wife
Sven (Still Woozy) and Amiya have been engaged since July 2020. It’s possible the couple have had a private marriage since then, though Sven has not been photographed wearing a wedding band.
Bad behavior
Bad Behavior is the title of a single by Remi Wolf and Austin Millz.
